      "question": "Find the area of a sector of a circle with radius $6$ $cm$ if the angle of the sector is $60^\\circ$. Use $\\pi = 3.14$.",
      "answer": "$18.84$ $cm^2$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the radius $r = 6$ $cm$ and central angle $\\theta = 60^\\circ$.",
          "Use the formula for the area of a sector: $A = \\frac{\\theta}{360^\\circ} \\times \\pi r^2$.",
          "Substitute the values and calculate the final result."
        ],
        "derivation": "$A = \\frac{60}{360} \\times 3.14 \\times 6^2 \\\\ A = \\frac{1}{6} \\times 3.14 \\times 36 \\\\ A = 3.14 \\times 6 \\\\ A = 18.84 \\text{ cm}^2$"
      },
