        "steps": [
          "Calculate the area of the sector $OAB$ with $\\theta = 90^\\circ$.",
          "Calculate the area of $\\triangle OAB$ which is a right-angled triangle with base and height equal to $10$ $cm$.",
          "Subtract the area of the triangle from the area of the sector to get the segment area."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\text{Area of sector} = \\frac{90}{360} \\times 3.14 \\times 10^2 = 78.5 \\text{ cm}^2 \\\\ \\text{Area of } \\triangle OAB = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 10 \\times 10 = 50 \\text{ cm}^2 \\\\ \\text{Area of segment} = 78.5 - 50 = 28.5 \\text{ cm}^2"
      },
