      "question": "The length of the minute hand of a clock is $14$ $cm$. Find the area swept by the minute hand in $5$ minutes.",
      "answer": "$51.33$ $cm^2$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Determine the angle swept in $60$ minutes ($360^\\circ$), so in $5$ minutes it is $30^\\circ$.",
          "Use the radius $r = 14$ $cm$.",
          "Apply the sector area formula."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\theta = \\frac{360}{60} \\times 5 = 30^\\circ \\\\ \\text{Area} = \\frac{30}{360} \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times 14 \\times 14 \\\\ \\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{12} \\times 22 \\times 2 \times 14 = \\frac{616}{12} = 51.33 \\text{ cm}^2"
      },
