      "question": "A horse is tethered to a peg at one corner of a square-shaped grass field of side $15$ $m$ by means of a $5$ $m$ long rope. Find the area of that part of the field in which the horse can graze.",
      "answer": "$19.625$ $m^2$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the shape as a quadrant of a circle with radius $r = 5$ $m$.",
          "The grazing area is the area of this quadrant.",
          "Calculate $\\frac{1}{4} \\times \\pi r^2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{4} \\times 3.14 \\times 5^2 \\\\ \\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{4} \\times 3.14 \\times 25 \\\\ \\text{Area} = 0.785 \\times 25 = 19.625 \\text{ m}^2"
      },
